subSubSection.paragraph:
Biology.
This species causes a marginal roll on the leaf of 

Impatiens platypetala

(
Balsaminaceae
) [
Figs 40a, b
]. The gall is figured in DvL & DvLR (1918, gall No. 599, Fig 599 [
Fig. 40a
]) and described by DvLR & DvL (1926) as follows. The margin of the leaf is rolled up for a small part of its length. The infected parts are white or yellowish and considerably thickened. The gall can be common locally.
